review_blob: This filthy bich had no lace...bare legs..she looked like dirty brown toilet water...but tasted as sweet as mothers milk.  Her snatch smelt wonderful.

review_blob: She is jungle black...and is perfect first thing in the morning..if your into that...referring to her coffee taste and aroma.  She starts with a nice creamy head that disapates but she leaves her lace all over hell.  She tastes very sweet...smoken (smokey flavor and smell) stout.
This bitch smells almost as good as she tastes.  Give her to much of your evening and she will F--k you up.  She leaves a beautiful head and has a fantastic carmel taste in her high alcohal snatch.

This blondy appears foggy with little diminishing head.  I like head, she doesn't cut it.  She's probably not supposed to given her style.  But I find it insulting none the less.  I find her taste interesting and distinctively dry.  Overall her golden puss was somewhat enjoyable...not as enjoyable as all you other snobs that have had her.

Watch out!  This bitch will bite you with her citricy snatch.  Carefull she might leave a mark.  She leaves lace as most dirty girls do and she looks excellent.  Not my favorite beer but can appreciate her quality.
Her appearance is average, ruby orange in color, she failed to shave her pits.  Her taste includes a slight hint of pumpkin carmel...Her snatch is a little bland...Overall she is solid.

Overall she is solid.  Is it fair that I drank her in the middle of the summer?  Haven't had a Winter Ale in a few months but it was a refreshing change from the brew I have been drinking lately.  She is dark in complection and leaves some trace of head.

This broad is excellent.  She gives great head...a thick foamy creamy mountain of head.  Her lips aare orangish yellow in color... her taste is similar to the single malt I had (and when I say had, I mean HAD) at Town Hall.
This bitch tastes of nastly puss...Mustard mixed with fruit...vomit.  She has a substansive appearnce...golden orange in color.  Her head is of dishwater.
This bitch has golden particles in her snatch...which i like.  She tastes of coffee and is dirty black in color with a dark golden diminishing head.
This dark bitch gives little head for a stout.  Her smell is excellent..coffee hint.  She is dirty in color..not the best offering at Sierra Nevada.
She has substance.  She don't give head but she does blow chiunk...as in chunchs of good stuff in beer.  Her tan is golden asn she retains some lace, she's filthy but just not great.

"Best enjoyed by 2/24/03"...I enjoyed on 2/20/03.  That made me a little nervous.  This beer was really good but more malt than the bitter and hoppy as I remembered her at a previous tasting.  Maybe the age of the bottle.  She gave and maintained good head.  One last thing she left lace which makes me want to come back for more.

Barepaw?  go back to the jungle.  The idea of IPA is bitterness.  This is about as mild as an IPA gets.  Excellent stank..solid beer smell.  She give good froathy head...orange brown with hints of some of some of the good stuff floating around in the bottle.
She tasted great.  I may keep her around and hammer her for an entire evening.  If you know what I mean.  I like when chunks float in my beer...it's intimidating.
Have you ever thought a girl was too sweet?  I experienced that at St. Paul Winterfest 2/8/03.  This is it.  ISH! she gave good head though.
Winterfest St. paul 2/8/03.  I am Irish so I may be biased...but she tasted good...she's a red who who wears lace.  A tough combo.
No bad for a pizza joint!  I had her in St. Paul at Winterfest 2/8/03.  She gave solid head was auburn in color and had a box that bites back..i like that!

review_blob: Another beer from Winterfest in St. Paul 2/8/03.  She gives some head...her taste is malt.
I got little head from her but she had a very tangy taste.  I had her in front of everyone at Winterfest in St Paul 2/8/03.
She gave excellent head but that's about it...she was tasteless..disappointed.
She appears dirty...which I like..She gives excellent head and maintains her dirty lace.  Taste is very citrusy.

My favorite cheap beer..kinda reminds me of that cheap date I would call in the middle of the night just to get laid.  Golden color, soap sud head...she doesn't give it for long.  Sour old rusty pipe taste to her.

She gives and maintains solid head.  She is also dressed in lace.  She is dark as night, which is kinky...and smells the warm camp fire I once smelt with my first lay...oh that's right...wrong venue.  Overall a little too much artificial taste (coffee ect.) for my taste.  Good beer if your looking for a caffeine fix.
Cool cap...kinda reminds me of a chastity belt. She doesn't give much head and is brown in color.  A descent beer but I was a little disappointed since it was packaged so well.
She gives absolutely no head..NONE!!!...which sucks, but not literally.  Her color is golden and smell is grainy..Overall a bland American Standard.
This German woman gives descent head and is dark in color.  Her most distinctive feature is her smell..I can smell her malt.  Her taste is too smooth...I like more bite.
She gives good head for one of Pete's girls. Her hair is auburn in color and she has a small bite of attitude.  Not enough form me to do again, at least for money. Later.
She gives excellent head and is extremely cloudy...her juice taste very sweet which is nice for some...but not me.

From the looks of it she may have a yeast infection (particles in liquid)and the smell appears to be of distinctive perfume trying to cover it up.  The smell might scare some but her taste is strong and hoppy.  She gives excellent foamy head.
She is an orange amber in color...she gives good head and leaves lots of lace.  She has a hoppy flavored snatch with a mild finish.  Solid.

I won this beer at Wawoods yuppy beer tasting.  Hef is a german bitch who gives good foamy head and wears lots of lace...she is really dirty.  her golden cloudy quality appearance distinquishes her.  she has a destinquishing taste that ends very smoothly. I like her yeast...so much so she may have an infection...which is a good thing. solid++
Her sweet bush is black as night smells of vanilla malt. She gives good head and lasts longer than most. Her taste is a sweet chocolate vanilla mix leaving little if any after taste...solid
She looks of an October orangish brown in color and give pretty weak head.  Her taste is pure malt with no hint of hops...her finish leaves you high and very dry..solid

She doesnt smell like much but she has a rich cinnamon/ginger taste to her snatch...so much so it gets sickening by the end of the beer.  Her lace has a wonderful sparkle emerging from a modest frothy head.
